<keyLead id="308895B8810AF10AFF212666FAB4FE75" pageId="19" pageNumber="52">
1. Protibia not swollen (
<figureCitation id="13422A08810AF10AFE752666FDF1FE9A" box="[489,562,312,338]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[189,232,1963,1989]" captionTargetBox="[196,1393,1008,1863]" captionTargetId="figure-206@4.[189,1399,999,1887]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 2. Spanglerelmis xiririca Polizei &amp; Bispo gen. et sp. nov., holotype, ♂ (MZSP31444). Habitus. A. Dorsal view (arrow showing the pattern of tomentum on femur). B. Ventral view. Scale bar = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6468149" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6468149/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="52">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
); hypomeron with a belt of tomentum near the suture (
<figureCitation id="13422A08810AF10AFB202666FAD9FE9A" box="[1212,1306,312,338]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="12.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,266,1794]" captionTargetId="figure-19@12.[189,1399,266,1794]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Fig. 7. Spanglerelmis xiririca Polizei &amp; Bispo gen. et sp. nov. under scanning electron microscope, ♀ (MZSP31481). Ventral view. A. Habitus. B. Hind leg (arrow showing the pattern of tomentum on femur). C. Prosternum and mesoventrite. D. Metaventrite and abdominal ventrites I–II. Scale bars = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6468159" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6468159/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="52">Fig. 7C</figureCitation>
); apical tarsomere as long as the four-preceding combined; abdominal ventrite 1 with a pair of carinae, ventrite 5 strongly emarginate laterally (
<figureCitation id="13422A08810AF10AFD5E2621FCDFFE51" box="[706,796,383,409]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[189,232,1963,1989]" captionTargetBox="[196,1393,1008,1863]" captionTargetId="figure-206@4.[189,1399,999,1887]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 2. Spanglerelmis xiririca Polizei &amp; Bispo gen. et sp. nov., holotype, ♂ (MZSP31444). Habitus. A. Dorsal view (arrow showing the pattern of tomentum on femur). B. Ventral view. Scale bar = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6468149" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6468149/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="52">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
)................................................................................ ..................................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="4C794D0E810AF10AFD7026FCFB7CFE75" authority="Polizei &amp; Bispo" authorityName="Polizei &amp; Costa &amp; Bispo" authorityYear="2022" box="[748,1215,418,445]" class="Insecta" family="Elmidae" genus="Spanglerelmis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xiririca" status="gen. et sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B90DEA9F810AF10AFD7026FCFC3EFE75" bold="true" box="[748,1021,418,445]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="52">Spanglerelmis xiririca</emphasis>
