</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC6368D810AF10AFF5D2699FAB4FDE0" blockId="19.[189,1399,312,869]" pageId="19" pageNumber="52">
<keyLead id="308895B8810AF10AFF5D2699FAB4FDE0" pageId="19" pageNumber="52">
– Protibia swollen (
<figureCitation id="13422A08810AF10AFE292699FDECFE29" box="[437,559,455,481]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[189,232,1857,1883]" captionTargetBox="[270,1336,267,1807]" captionTargetId="figure-12@3.[240,1346,262,1814]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 1. A–D. Spanglerelmis femoralis (Hinton, 1940) gen. et comb. nov., holotype, ♂ (NHMUK 010583892). A–C. Habitus. A. Dorsal view. B. Ventral view. C. Lateral view. D. Aedeagus in ventral view. E–H. Microcylloepus ochus Hinton, 1940, holotype, ♂(NHMUK 010583871). E–G. Habitus. E. Dorsal view (arrows showing the pattern of tomentum on femur). F. Ventral view. G. Lateral view. H. Aedeagus in ventral view. Scale bars: A–C, E–G = 0.5 mm; D, H = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6468147" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6468147/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="52">Figs 1B, F</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13422A08810AF10AFDA42699FD40FE29" box="[568,643,455,481]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="16.[189,232,1928,1954]" captionTargetBox="[202,1384,280,1779]" captionTargetId="figure-19@16.[189,1399,262,1787]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Fig. 9. Spanglerelmis timburi Polizei &amp; Bispo gen. et sp. nov. holotype, ♂ (MZSP31520). A–B. Habitus. A. Dorsal view (arrows showing the pattern of tomentum on femur). B. Ventral view. C–D. Aedeagus in ventral view. E. Aedeagus in lateral view. Scale bars: A–B = 0.5 mm; C–E = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6468163" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6468163/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="52">9A–B</figureCitation>
); hypomeron without a belt of tomentum near the suture (
<figureCitation id="13422A08810AF10AFA8F2699FF3AFDCD" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[189,232,1857,1883]" captionTargetBox="[270,1336,267,1807]" captionTargetId="figure-12@3.[240,1346,262,1814]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 1. A–D. Spanglerelmis femoralis (Hinton, 1940) gen. et comb. nov., holotype, ♂ (NHMUK 010583892). A–C. Habitus. A. Dorsal view. B. Ventral view. C. Lateral view. D. Aedeagus in ventral view. E–H. Microcylloepus ochus Hinton, 1940, holotype, ♂(NHMUK 010583871). E–G. Habitus. E. Dorsal view (arrows showing the pattern of tomentum on femur). F. Ventral view. G. Lateral view. H. Aedeagus in ventral view. Scale bars: A–C, E–G = 0.5 mm; D, H = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6468147" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6468147/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="52">Figs 1B, F</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13422A08810AF10AFE9426B5FEEEFDCD" box="[264,301,491,517]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="16.[189,232,1928,1954]" captionTargetBox="[202,1384,280,1779]" captionTargetId="figure-19@16.[189,1399,262,1787]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Fig. 9. Spanglerelmis timburi Polizei &amp; Bispo gen. et sp. nov. holotype, ♂ (MZSP31520). A–B. Habitus. A. Dorsal view (arrows showing the pattern of tomentum on femur). B. Ventral view. C–D. Aedeagus in ventral view. E. Aedeagus in lateral view. Scale bars: A–B = 0.5 mm; C–E = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6468163" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6468163/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="52">9B</figureCitation>
); apical tarsomere shorter than the four-preceding combined; abdominal ventrite 1 without carinae, ventrite 5 moderately emarginate laterally (
<figureCitation id="13422A08810AF10AFCD52550FC60FDE0" box="[841,931,526,552]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="16.[189,232,1928,1954]" captionTargetBox="[202,1384,280,1779]" captionTargetId="figure-19@16.[189,1399,262,1787]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Fig. 9. Spanglerelmis timburi Polizei &amp; Bispo gen. et sp. nov. holotype, ♂ (MZSP31520). A–B. Habitus. A. Dorsal view (arrows showing the pattern of tomentum on femur). B. Ventral view. C–D. Aedeagus in ventral view. E. Aedeagus in lateral view. Scale bars: A–B = 0.5 mm; C–E = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6468163" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6468163/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="52">Fig. 9B</figureCitation>
) ........................................................... 2
