<keyStep id="308D2E28810AF10AFF21250EFAB4FCAD" pageId="19" pageNumber="52">
<paragraph id="8BC6368D810AF10AFF21250EFAB4FD1E" blockId="19.[189,1399,312,869]" pageId="19" pageNumber="52">
<keyLead id="308895B8810AF10AFF21250EFAB4FD1E" pageId="19" pageNumber="52">
2. Elytron with first puncture on interval IV bigger and deeper than any others (
<figureCitation id="13422A08810AF10AFB02250EFAC3FDA2" box="[1182,1280,592,618]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="16.[189,232,1928,1954]" captionTargetBox="[202,1384,280,1779]" captionTargetId="figure-19@16.[189,1399,262,1787]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Fig. 9. Spanglerelmis timburi Polizei &amp; Bispo gen. et sp. nov. holotype, ♂ (MZSP31520). A–B. Habitus. A. Dorsal view (arrows showing the pattern of tomentum on femur). B. Ventral view. C–D. Aedeagus in ventral view. E. Aedeagus in lateral view. Scale bars: A–B = 0.5 mm; C–E = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6468163" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6468163/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="52">Fig. 9A</figureCitation>
); setae of the protarsomeres no longer than on the other legs (males); metatibia without spur; phallobase 1.5× as long as penis, approximately 2.5× as long as wide; penis 4× as long as wide (9C– D) ................................................................. 
<taxonomicName id="4C794D0E810AF10AFD7025E5FB7CFD1E" authority="Polizei &amp; Bispo" authorityName="Polizei &amp; Costa &amp; Bispo" authorityYear="2022" box="[748,1215,699,726]" class="Insecta" family="Elmidae" genus="Spanglerelmis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="timburi" status="gen. et sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B90DEA9F810AF10AFD7025E5FC3EFD1E" bold="true" box="[748,1021,699,726]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="52">Spanglerelmis timburi</emphasis>
Polizei &amp; Bispo
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A23E57E4810AF10AFB5B25E2FAB4FD1E" box="[1223,1399,700,726]" pageId="19" pageNumber="52" rank="species">gen. et sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC6368D810AF10AFF5D25BEFAB4FCAD" blockId="19.[189,1399,312,869]" pageId="19" pageNumber="52">
<keyLead id="308895B8810AF10AFF5D25BEFAB4FCAD" pageId="19" pageNumber="52">
– Elytron with first puncture on interval IV not bigger and deeper than any others (
<figureCitation id="13422A08810AF10AFB7C2581FAABFD32" box="[1248,1384,735,762]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[189,232,1857,1883]" captionTargetBox="[270,1336,267,1807]" captionTargetId="figure-12@3.[240,1346,262,1814]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 1. A–D. Spanglerelmis femoralis (Hinton, 1940) gen. et comb. nov., holotype, ♂ (NHMUK 010583892). A–C. Habitus. A. Dorsal view. B. Ventral view. C. Lateral view. D. Aedeagus in ventral view. E–H. Microcylloepus ochus Hinton, 1940, holotype, ♂(NHMUK 010583871). E–G. Habitus. E. Dorsal view (arrows showing the pattern of tomentum on femur). F. Ventral view. G. Lateral view. H. Aedeagus in ventral view. Scale bars: A–C, E–G = 0.5 mm; D, H = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6468147" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6468147/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="52">Fig. 1A, E</figureCitation>
); setae of the protarsomeres longer than on the other legs (males); metatibia with a curved spur (males); phallobase 2× as long as penis, approximately 4× as long as wide; penis 3× as long as wide ............................................................ 
<taxonomicName id="4C794D0E810AF10AFD252414FB5BFCAD" authority="(Hinton, 1940)" authorityName="Polizei &amp; Costa &amp; Bispo" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Hinton" baseAuthorityYear="1940" box="[697,1176,842,869]" class="Insecta" family="Elmidae" genus="Spanglerelmis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="femoralis" status="gen. et comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="B90DEA9F810AF10AFD252414FC21FCAD" bold="true" box="[697,994,842,869]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="52">Spanglerelmis femoralis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFE84B7C810AF10AFC6E2415FB53FCAD" author="Hinton H. E." box="[1010,1168,843,869]" pageId="19" pageNumber="52" pagination="236 - 247" refId="ref11451" refString="Hinton H. E. 1940. XIX - On some new Brazilian Microcylloepus, with a key to the species (Coleoptera, Elmidae). The Annals and Magazine of Natural History 11 (32): 236 - 247. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 03745481.1940.9723672" type="journal article" year="1940">Hinton, 1940</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
