<subSubSection id="C3636506810AF10AFF2124D2FBACFB3C" pageId="19" pageNumber="52" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BC6368D810AF10AFF2124D2FE42FC6F" blockId="19.[189,385,908,935]" box="[189,385,908,935]" pageId="19" pageNumber="52">
<heading id="D08E81E1810AF10AFF2124D2FE42FC6F" bold="true" box="[189,385,908,935]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="19" pageNumber="52" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B90DEA9F810AF10AFF2124D2FE42FC6F" bold="true" box="[189,385,908,935]" pageId="19" pageNumber="52">Biological notes</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC6368D810AF10AFF2124E2FBACFB3C" blockId="19.[188,1399,956,1269]" pageId="19" pageNumber="52">
<taxonomicName id="4C794D0E810AF10AFF2124E2FEA5FC1E" authorityName="Polizei &amp; Costa &amp; Bispo" authorityYear="2022" box="[189,358,956,982]" class="Insecta" family="Elmidae" genus="Spanglerelmis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90DEA9F810AF10AFF2124E2FEA5FC1E" box="[189,358,956,982]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="52">Spanglerelmis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is only recorded from the Atlantic rainforest (
<figureCitation id="13422A08810AF10AFCE724E2FC11FC1E" box="[891,978,956,982]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="18.[189,231,1752,1778]" captionTargetBox="[265,1322,266,1699]" captionTargetId="figure-19@18.[262,1333,264,1706]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Fig. 10. Distribution records for Spanglerelmis Polizei &amp; Bispo gen. nov. A. Map of Brazil highlighting the São Paulo and Santa Catarina States, showing the localities of Spanglerelmis gen. nov. B–D. Locality of Spanglerelmis xiririca gen. et sp. nov. B. Parque Estadual Caverna do Diabo, Eldorado, São Paulo State, Brazil (type locality) (24°38′00.7ʺ S, 048°24′32.7ʺ W). C. Parque Estadual de Intervales, Ribeirão Grande, São Paulo State, Brazil (24°16′16ʺ S, 048°25′31ʺ W). D. Echaporã, São Paulo State, Brazil (22°25′06.9ʺ S, 050°12′0.9ʺ W). E. Type locality of Spanglerelmis timburi gen. et sp. nov. Timburi, São Paulo State, Brazil (23°11′01.6ʺ S, 049°37′49.2ʺ W). F. Type locality of Spanglerelmis femoralis gen. et comb. nov. Nova Teutônia (currently county of Seara), Santa Catarina State, Brazil (27°09′42.5′′ S, 052°25′28.5′′ W)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6468165" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6468165/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="52">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
). Most of the material was collected by the authors during expeditions to unimpacted streams in the 
<collectingRegion id="49BDF86F810AF10AFC0424BEFB92FC32" box="[920,1105,992,1018]" country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo" pageId="19" pageNumber="52">São Paulo State</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F36E761D810AF10AFBC724BEFB65FC32" box="[1115,1190,992,1018]" name="Brazil" pageId="19" pageNumber="52">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, in the years 1999 to 2000 and 2013, where a high diversity of aquatic beetles, mostly of the family 
<taxonomicName id="4C794D0E810AF10AFBFD235DFB05FBD5" authorityName="Curtis" authorityYear="1830" box="[1121,1222,1027,1053]" class="Insecta" family="Elmidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Elmidae</taxonomicName>
, was collected. Samples containing the two new species were collected from streams with high oxygen concentrations and rocky bottoms (
<figureCitation id="13422A08810AF10AFE302315FDF4FBAD" box="[428,567,1099,1125]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="18.[189,231,1752,1778]" captionTargetBox="[265,1322,266,1699]" captionTargetId="figure-19@18.[262,1333,264,1706]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Fig. 10. Distribution records for Spanglerelmis Polizei &amp; Bispo gen. nov. A. Map of Brazil highlighting the São Paulo and Santa Catarina States, showing the localities of Spanglerelmis gen. nov. B–D. Locality of Spanglerelmis xiririca gen. et sp. nov. B. Parque Estadual Caverna do Diabo, Eldorado, São Paulo State, Brazil (type locality) (24°38′00.7ʺ S, 048°24′32.7ʺ W). C. Parque Estadual de Intervales, Ribeirão Grande, São Paulo State, Brazil (24°16′16ʺ S, 048°25′31ʺ W). D. Echaporã, São Paulo State, Brazil (22°25′06.9ʺ S, 050°12′0.9ʺ W). E. Type locality of Spanglerelmis timburi gen. et sp. nov. Timburi, São Paulo State, Brazil (23°11′01.6ʺ S, 049°37′49.2ʺ W). F. Type locality of Spanglerelmis femoralis gen. et comb. nov. Nova Teutônia (currently county of Seara), Santa Catarina State, Brazil (27°09′42.5′′ S, 052°25′28.5′′ W)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6468165" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6468165/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="52">Fig. 10B–E</figureCitation>
) in Parque Estadual Caverna do Diabo (Eldorado) (
<figureCitation id="13422A08810AF10AFB3E2315FACDFBAD" box="[1186,1294,1099,1125]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="18.[189,231,1752,1778]" captionTargetBox="[265,1322,266,1699]" captionTargetId="figure-19@18.[262,1333,264,1706]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Fig. 10. Distribution records for Spanglerelmis Polizei &amp; Bispo gen. nov. A. Map of Brazil highlighting the São Paulo and Santa Catarina States, showing the localities of Spanglerelmis gen. nov. B–D. Locality of Spanglerelmis xiririca gen. et sp. nov. B. Parque Estadual Caverna do Diabo, Eldorado, São Paulo State, Brazil (type locality) (24°38′00.7ʺ S, 048°24′32.7ʺ W). C. Parque Estadual de Intervales, Ribeirão Grande, São Paulo State, Brazil (24°16′16ʺ S, 048°25′31ʺ W). D. Echaporã, São Paulo State, Brazil (22°25′06.9ʺ S, 050°12′0.9ʺ W). E. Type locality of Spanglerelmis timburi gen. et sp. nov. Timburi, São Paulo State, Brazil (23°11′01.6ʺ S, 049°37′49.2ʺ W). F. Type locality of Spanglerelmis femoralis gen. et comb. nov. Nova Teutônia (currently county of Seara), Santa Catarina State, Brazil (27°09′42.5′′ S, 052°25′28.5′′ W)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6468165" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6468165/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="52">Fig. 10B</figureCitation>
); Parque Estadual Intervales (Ribeirão Grande) (
<figureCitation id="13422A08810AF10AFD112331FD3AFB41" box="[653,761,1135,1161]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="18.[189,231,1752,1778]" captionTargetBox="[265,1322,266,1699]" captionTargetId="figure-19@18.[262,1333,264,1706]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Fig. 10. Distribution records for Spanglerelmis Polizei &amp; Bispo gen. nov. A. Map of Brazil highlighting the São Paulo and Santa Catarina States, showing the localities of Spanglerelmis gen. nov. B–D. Locality of Spanglerelmis xiririca gen. et sp. nov. B. Parque Estadual Caverna do Diabo, Eldorado, São Paulo State, Brazil (type locality) (24°38′00.7ʺ S, 048°24′32.7ʺ W). C. Parque Estadual de Intervales, Ribeirão Grande, São Paulo State, Brazil (24°16′16ʺ S, 048°25′31ʺ W). D. Echaporã, São Paulo State, Brazil (22°25′06.9ʺ S, 050°12′0.9ʺ W). E. Type locality of Spanglerelmis timburi gen. et sp. nov. Timburi, São Paulo State, Brazil (23°11′01.6ʺ S, 049°37′49.2ʺ W). F. Type locality of Spanglerelmis femoralis gen. et comb. nov. Nova Teutônia (currently county of Seara), Santa Catarina State, Brazil (27°09′42.5′′ S, 052°25′28.5′′ W)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6468165" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6468165/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="52">Fig. 10C</figureCitation>
); the region of Echaporã (
<figureCitation id="13422A08810AF10AFBB02331FB59FB41" box="[1068,1178,1135,1161]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="18.[189,231,1752,1778]" captionTargetBox="[265,1322,266,1699]" captionTargetId="figure-19@18.[262,1333,264,1706]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Fig. 10. Distribution records for Spanglerelmis Polizei &amp; Bispo gen. nov. A. Map of Brazil highlighting the São Paulo and Santa Catarina States, showing the localities of Spanglerelmis gen. nov. B–D. Locality of Spanglerelmis xiririca gen. et sp. nov. B. Parque Estadual Caverna do Diabo, Eldorado, São Paulo State, Brazil (type locality) (24°38′00.7ʺ S, 048°24′32.7ʺ W). C. Parque Estadual de Intervales, Ribeirão Grande, São Paulo State, Brazil (24°16′16ʺ S, 048°25′31ʺ W). D. Echaporã, São Paulo State, Brazil (22°25′06.9ʺ S, 050°12′0.9ʺ W). E. Type locality of Spanglerelmis timburi gen. et sp. nov. Timburi, São Paulo State, Brazil (23°11′01.6ʺ S, 049°37′49.2ʺ W). F. Type locality of Spanglerelmis femoralis gen. et comb. nov. Nova Teutônia (currently county of Seara), Santa Catarina State, Brazil (27°09′42.5′′ S, 052°25′28.5′′ W)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6468165" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6468165/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="52">Fig. 10D</figureCitation>
); and the region of Timburi (
<figureCitation id="13422A08810AF10AFEB023CCFE56FB65" box="[300,405,1170,1197]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="18.[189,231,1752,1778]" captionTargetBox="[265,1322,266,1699]" captionTargetId="figure-19@18.[262,1333,264,1706]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Fig. 10. Distribution records for Spanglerelmis Polizei &amp; Bispo gen. nov. A. Map of Brazil highlighting the São Paulo and Santa Catarina States, showing the localities of Spanglerelmis gen. nov. B–D. Locality of Spanglerelmis xiririca gen. et sp. nov. B. Parque Estadual Caverna do Diabo, Eldorado, São Paulo State, Brazil (type locality) (24°38′00.7ʺ S, 048°24′32.7ʺ W). C. Parque Estadual de Intervales, Ribeirão Grande, São Paulo State, Brazil (24°16′16ʺ S, 048°25′31ʺ W). D. Echaporã, São Paulo State, Brazil (22°25′06.9ʺ S, 050°12′0.9ʺ W). E. Type locality of Spanglerelmis timburi gen. et sp. nov. Timburi, São Paulo State, Brazil (23°11′01.6ʺ S, 049°37′49.2ʺ W). F. Type locality of Spanglerelmis femoralis gen. et comb. nov. Nova Teutônia (currently county of Seara), Santa Catarina State, Brazil (27°09′42.5′′ S, 052°25′28.5′′ W)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6468165" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6468165/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="52">Fig. 10E</figureCitation>
). These streams are in basins with undisturbed vegetation and in elevations that range from 
<quantity id="4C819B68810AF10AFF6023E8FE85FB19" box="[252,326,1206,1233]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.52" pageId="19" pageNumber="52" unit="m" value="452.0">452 m</quantity>
to 
<specimenCount id="9D7FFD04810AF10AFEF723E8FE7FFB19" box="[363,444,1206,1233]" pageId="19" pageNumber="52" type="generic">
<quantity id="4C819B68810AF10AFEF723E8FE7BFB19" box="[363,440,1206,1233]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.2" pageId="19" pageNumber="52" unit="m" value="820.0">820 m</quantity>
.
</specimenCount>
In general, the specimens were collected in riffles at a depth of 
<quantity id="4C819B68810AF10AFB3A23E8FB2AFB19" box="[1190,1257,1206,1233]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="19" pageNumber="52" unit="m" value="0.1">0.1 m</quantity>
to 
<quantity id="4C819B68810AF10AFA9223E8FA90FB19" box="[1294,1363,1206,1233]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="19" pageNumber="52" unit="m" value="0.5">0.5 m</quantity>
, in streams with different slopes and with alternating pools and riffles (
<figureCitation id="13422A08810AF10AFC492384FBA1FB3C" box="[981,1122,1242,1268]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="18.[189,231,1752,1778]" captionTargetBox="[265,1322,266,1699]" captionTargetId="figure-19@18.[262,1333,264,1706]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Fig. 10. Distribution records for Spanglerelmis Polizei &amp; Bispo gen. nov. A. Map of Brazil highlighting the São Paulo and Santa Catarina States, showing the localities of Spanglerelmis gen. nov. B–D. Locality of Spanglerelmis xiririca gen. et sp. nov. B. Parque Estadual Caverna do Diabo, Eldorado, São Paulo State, Brazil (type locality) (24°38′00.7ʺ S, 048°24′32.7ʺ W). C. Parque Estadual de Intervales, Ribeirão Grande, São Paulo State, Brazil (24°16′16ʺ S, 048°25′31ʺ W). D. Echaporã, São Paulo State, Brazil (22°25′06.9ʺ S, 050°12′0.9ʺ W). E. Type locality of Spanglerelmis timburi gen. et sp. nov. Timburi, São Paulo State, Brazil (23°11′01.6ʺ S, 049°37′49.2ʺ W). F. Type locality of Spanglerelmis femoralis gen. et comb. nov. Nova Teutônia (currently county of Seara), Santa Catarina State, Brazil (27°09′42.5′′ S, 052°25′28.5′′ W)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6468165" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6468165/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="52">Fig. 10B–E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
